OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F434A1776438666
OL,3,CGlyn Razzell: Murderer who refuses to
OL,4,Csay where wife's body is granted parole
OL,6,FConvicted murderer Glyn Razzell who
OL,7,Fhas never revealed where he hid his
OL,8,Fwife's body has been granted parole.
OL,10,FGlyn Razzell, 64, was found guilty of
OL,11,Fthe murder of his 41-year-old
OL,12,Festranged wife Linda Razzell, 41, in
OL,13,F2003 and sentenced to life in prison.
OL,15,FHe was one of the first prisoners to
OL,16,Fbe affected by Helen's Law, which aims
OL,17,Fto make it harder for killers to get
OL,18,Fparole if they refuse to reveal where
OL,19,Fthey hid their victim's body.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G1/6
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
