PN,43405
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F434A1776438666
OL,3,CGlyn Razzell: Murderer who refuses to
OL,4,Csay where wife's body is granted parole
OL,6,FA spokesperson for the Parole Board
OL,7,Fcontinued: "A panel will carefully
OL,8,Fexamine a huge range of evidence,
OL,9,Fincluding details of the original
OL,10,Fcrime, and any evidence of behaviour
OL,11,Fchange, as well as explore the harm
OL,12,Fdone and impact the crime has had on
OL,13,Fthe victims.
OL,15,F"Members read and digest hundreds of
OL,16,Fpages of evidence and reports in the
OL,17,Flead up to an oral hearing.
OL,26,@wD@AOU
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/6
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,435,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43406
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F434A1776438666
OL,3,CGlyn Razzell: Murderer who refuses to
OL,4,Csay where wife's body is granted parole
OL,6,F"Evidence from witnesses such as
OL,7,Fprobation officers, psychiatrists and
OL,8,Fpsychologists, officials supervising
OL,9,Fthe offender in prison as well as
OL,10,Fvictim personal statements may be
OL,11,Fgiven at the hearing.
OL,13,F"It is standard for the prisoner and
OL,14,Fwitnesses to be questioned at length
OL,15,Fduring the hearing which often lasts a
OL,16,Ffull day or more.
OL,18,F''Parole reviews are undertaken
OL,19,Fthoroughly and with extreme care.
OL,20,FProtecting the public is our number
OL,21,Fone priority."
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/6
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
